I"(<p>This aspect covers the proof of control of all funds that should be held by the information system. There have been known cases where information systems that should be operating with a full reserve of user funds have been operating with a fraction of that reserve instead leading to an inability of the system to cover simultaneous withdrawals by all users. These <a href="../Definitions#proof-of-reserve">proofs of reserve</a> provide assurance to the public that all funds are available to the system which eliminates the risks of fund loss.</p>
